# Jodconvertor docker container


Simple jodconvertor 2.2 container

# Usage with docker compose

```
version: '2'
services:
  jodconvertor:
    restart: always
    image: jetpulp/jodconvertor
    volumes:
      - ./applicationContext.xml:/app/jodconverter-tomcat-2.2.2/webapps/converter/WEB-INF/applicationContext.xml
      - ./tmp:/app/jodconverter-tomcat-2.2.2/temp/
    ports:
      - 8099:8080
    links:
      - libreoffice
  libreoffice:
    restart: always
    image: jetpulp/libreoffice:5.3
    volumes:
      - ./tmp:/app/jodconverter-tomcat-2.2.2/temp/
```

The applicationContext.xml is note mandatory but can help you to customize the libreoffice IP adresse. You can find an sample file here : https://github.com/jetpulp/docker-jodconvertor/blob/master/applicationContext.xml


